ulid-c
------------------------------------------
This is a library for generating and handling Universally Unique
Lexicographically Sortable Identifiers (ULIDs). On modern hardware running
Linux, it can generate 68 million ULIDs per second (50 cycles per ULID).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libulid-c-devel-0+git20200118-1bl2
  libulid-c0-0+git20200118-1bl2
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/skeeto/ulid-c

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/skeeto/ulid-c.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ulid-c-0+git20200118-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ulid-c-0+git20200118-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ulid-c-0+git20200118-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ulid-c-0+git20200118-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libulid-c0-0+git20200118-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libulid-c-devel-0+git20200118-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(ulid-c)
  /usr/bin/ulidgen.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/ulid-c.README
  /usr/share/doc/ulid-c/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/ulid-c/UNLICENSE

(libulid-c0)
  /usr/bin/cygulid-c-0.dll

(libulid-c-devel)
  /usr/include/ulid.h
  /usr/lib/libulid-c.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/ulid-c.pc

